comp4335 wireless mesh and sensor networks wireless mesh networks wmns and wireless sensor networks wsns are two emerging wireless technologies which will have important impact in the future in fact the significance of wsns has led to it being labelled as one of the most important technologies in the 21st century.this course will cover the fundamental design principles behind building scalable wmns and wsns the following aspects on wireless mesh and sensor networks will be covered medium access control protocol routing protocol design transport layer issues middleware application and security it will also cover case studies on deploying wireless mesh and sensor networks.this course includes a laboratory component and minor design project it may also include guest lectures from leading industrial and academic researchers 